I"¶<p>I use empty spaces in the dock to group applications in the dock. My dock looks like this:<br />
<a href="http://swift.eltanin.uberspace.de/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Screen-Shot-2015-07-28-at-20.07.46.png"><img src="/assets/Screen-Shot-2015-07-28-at-20.07.46.png" alt="Screen Shot 2015-07-28 at 20.07.46" width="1020" height="36" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-756" /></a></p>
<p>To add an empty space, open the Terminal and type in</p>
<pre class="lang:sh decode:true ">defaults write com.apple.dock persistent-apps -array-add '{"tile-type"="spacer-tile";}'
killall Dock</pre>
<p>You can drag and drop an empty space like application icons. To remove it, drag it from the dock.</p>
